#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-unit
This function is not yet available

Extracts the scroll delta unit of a scroll event.

The unit will always be C<GDK_SCROLL_UNIT_WHEEL> if the scroll direction is not
C<GDK_SCROLL_SMOOTH>.

=begin code
method get-unit (--> GdkScrollUnit  )
=end code

Return value; the scroll unit.. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for get-unit

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 is-stop

Check whether a scroll event is a stop scroll event.

Scroll sequences with smooth scroll information may provide
a stop scroll event once the interaction with the device finishes,
e.g. by lifting a finger. This stop scroll event is the signal
that a widget may trigger kinetic scrolling based on the current
velocity.

Stop scroll events always have a delta of 0/0.

=begin code
method is-stop (--> Bool )
=end code

Return value; C<True> if the event is a scroll stop event. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for is-stop

=end comment

=end pod

